        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 7 at 4:44AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 443 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles east of Dilley, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Charlotte, Christine, Goldfinch, Hindes, and Davis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
